# Ruby on Rails API Documentation

> Per-version API reference for Ruby on Rails and the official ecosystem
> gems (Turbo, Stimulus, Kamal, the Solid trio, and more). Every class,
> module, method, constant, and attribute has a stable per-entity URL,
> versioned back to Rails 2.2.

## Machine-readable docs

Append `.md` to any entity URL — or send `Accept: text/markdown` — to get
a clean Markdown document (title, signature, documentation, source link,
version availability) with none of the page chrome:

  <%= root_url.chomp("/") %>/v<%= @stable&.channel || "8.1.2" %>/active_record/persistence/save.md

## URL scheme

  /v<VERSION>/<framework>/<path>            class or module page
  /v<VERSION>/<framework>/<path>/<method>   instance method
  /v<VERSION>/<framework>/<path>/<method>.class   class method
  /<gem>/v<VERSION>/<path>                  ecosystem gem (turbo-rails, kamal, …)

Version-less URLs (e.g. /active_record/persistence/save) redirect to the
current stable release.

